HACK v. DADY. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. January 27, 1911.) Appeal from Kings County Court. Action by Henry Hack against Michael J. Dady. From a judgment for plaintiff, and from an order denying a motion for a new trial, defendant appeals. Affirmed. See, also, 136 App. Div. 888, 119 N. Y. Supp. 1127.

Argued before JENKS, P. J„ and BURR, THOMAS, CARR, and RICH, JJ.

Frank V. Johnson and William F. Kiefer, for appellant. Frederick N. Van Zandt, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

Judgment and order of the County Court of Kings County unanimously affirmed, with costs, on the authority of Julia Hack v. Dady (decided herewith) 127 N. Y. Supp. 22.
